Solution_Comment__c:
The customer had 2 issues in a row: the service account was getting locked out and this error appeared if the account was in a normal state:

Stealthbits.StealthAUDIT.DataCollectors.FSAA.FSAAException: Unable to start scan: Invalid provider type specified.

The actions are the same as described in this article:
https://helpcenter.netwrix.com/bundle/z-kb-articles-salesforce/page/kA0Qk0000000WSvKAM.html

The customer deleted the FSAA Certificate Authority Store and FSAA Client Certificate Store certificates on NEA host and the scan was initiated successfully.
